                                    <div class="gtr"><a title="Bookmark this section" href="#UT22084-058-002-45" data-bookmark="The Questions of the Nāga King Sāgara (3) / g.­3" class="milestone">g.­3</a></div>
                                    <div class="item-content">
                                        <h3><span class="term text-en" lang="en">contaminated phenomena</span></h3>
                                        <div>
                                            <ul class="list-inline inline-dots">
                                                <li><span class="term text-wy" lang="bo-LTN">zag pa dang bcas pa</span></li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            <ul class="list-inline inline-dots">
                                                <li><span class="term text-bo" lang="bo">ཟག་པ་དང་བཅས་པ།</span></li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            <ul class="list-inline inline-dots">
                                                <li><span class="term text-sa" lang="sa-LTN">sāsrava</span></li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="footer">
                                            <p class="definition">The phenomena of saṃsāra. <span class="ignore">Contaminated phenomena</span> are those influenced by the defilements (<em class="text-sa" lang="sa-LTN">kleśa</em>, <em class="text-wy" lang="bo-LTN">nyon mongs</em>) and karma. Thus, e.g., even virtues that are under the influence of defilements, like ignorance, are categorized as contaminated in this way.</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="footer hidden-print" role="navigation" aria-label="Locations of this term in the text">
                                            <h4 class="heading">Located in 4 passages in the translation:</h4>
